places.title: Small Tower
places.description:
Everybody knows about Tour Eiffel, but I was surprised to find out (as we was getting closer & closer to the big one) that, there is another tower beside the famous one. Here my pictures to better understand what I am trying to say...
Of course, Equestrian Police is watching, for safe of tourists...

places.title: Creperie

places.urlhtml: Vedettes de Paris, croisières sur la Seine.
places.title: Vedettes de Paris, croisières sur la Seine.
places.description:
Les Vedettes de Paris proposent des croisières touristiques sur la Seine. Les croisières sont faites à bord de bateaux chics à faible capacité. Idéales pour apercevoir Paris par les eaux, cette croisière qualitative offre en plus d'un joli bateau avec un bar à son bord, un réel attrait culturel. 1 heure de croisière depuis le port de Suffren pour faire demi-tour à l'Ile Saint Louis permette à ses passagers d'admirer quelques des plus beaux monuments de la Capitale tels que la Tour Eiffel, Notre Dame de Paris, le Trocadéro, le Grand Palais.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=53w2CT9S9SE

places.title: Stadium Emile Anthoine
places.description: Centre sportif Émile Anthoine (Emile Antoine Sports Center) at the base of the Eiffel Tower.

places.title: Musée du quai Branly
places.description: The Musée du quai Branly, known in English as the Quai Branly Museum, nicknamed MQB, is a museum in Paris, France that features indigenous art, cultures and civilizations from Africa, Asia, Oceania, and the Americas. The museum is located at 37, quai Branly - portail Debilly, 75007 Paris, France, situated close to the Eiffel Tower.

places.title: Public Restroom
places.description: Underground public restroom. Stairs are located in center of tree-lined path / parking median.  Closes at 18:00 (6pm) even during summer, when there are still many people in the area. If desperate, have a friend keep watch at the top of the stairs while you pee at the bottom... you won't be the first. Otherwise, buy an overpriced drink at one of the cafes on the corner and use their restroom. (There are also public restrooms at the base of the Eiffel Tower, but they close at the same time!)

places.title: Champ de Mars
places.description: A Large garden between the Eiffel Tower and the Ecole Militaire (military school). It used to be wider, but was thinned down. It was also the marching ground for students at the Ecole Militaire. Before it's thinning down, Gustave Eiffel, creator of the nearby tower, used to land dirigibles on it.

comments.name: Discover
comments.message: In Saint-Petersburg we have a Champ de Mars (Марсово Поле) too.

places.title: Trocadero
places.description: The Trocadéro, site of the Palais de Chaillot, is an area of Paris, in the 16th arrondissement, across the Seine from the Eiffel Tower. The hill of the Trocadéro is the hill of Chaillot, a former village.

places.title: Palais de Chaillot
places.description: Complex built for the 1937 World's Fair. Today houses a number of museums, including the Musée national de la Marine (naval museum), Cité de l'Architecture et du Patrimoine and the Musée de l'Homme (ethnology). This structure is somewhat taller than the surrounding buildings and stands out because of its monumental size.

places.title: Cadran, hôtel gourmand
places.description:
Our hotel & in-hotel store are perfectly located, just a few minutes from the Eiffel Tower, Invalides, the Rodin museum, Musée d'Orsay and the Champs- Elysées. Come to our chocolate bar & store and taste our chocolates, macaroons, marshmallows and hot chocolate drink, reclining in a comfortable armchair or to go. 
http://www.cadranhotel.com/hotel.html 

10 Rue du Champ de Mars 75007 Paris

places.title: Hotel Prince
places.description: Hotel Prince enjoys a unique location in Paris, in the immediate proximity of the Eiffel Tower, in the heart of one of the most prestigious Parisian districts.

comments.name: Fresnel
comments.message: Stayed here Sept. 2007, nothing fancy but great location near the Eiffel Tower. Metro is across the street and Rue Cler with markets and restaurants are just a block away.

places.title: Hotel Gavarni - Green Hotels Paris
places.description:
It is perfectly located near the Eiffel Tower and the OECD and 10 min away from the Champs-Elysées. The hotel involves itself in a city ecotourism project of sustainable development
and environment protection : 100% carbon balanced, 100% renewable energy,
100% eco-friendly detergents, organic and fair trade breakfast...
Our measures and commitment have allowed us to become the first independent hotel in Paris to be awarded the European Ecolabel.

places.title: Bateaux Mouches
places.description: Bateaux Mouches gives an opportunity for people take a boating cruise on the river Seine. The ride takes about 1 1/2 and shows several impotant places in paris from the riverside view. One can see Eiffel tower, Notre Dame, and replica of Statue of Liberty and other places.

places.description: En août 2012, Société Occasion et Location Indre (SOLI) occupe le 1 rue Gustave Eiffel dans la ZA "Les Chevaliers".

places.title: Maria Pia of Savoy bridge
places.description: The Maria Pia bridge (Ponte Maria Pia) is a railway bridge built in 1877 by Gustave Eiffel in Porto, Portugal. Built of wrought iron, its two-hinged crescent arch carries the railway line to Lisbon for 353m across the River Douro at a height of 60m.

places.title: Nyugati pályaudvar (Nyugati Railway Station)
places.description: One of the oldest railway stations in Budapest, opened in 1877. The plans of the railway station were made by the Austrian August de Serres and the firm of Gustave Eiffel.
